==== Mast Cell Activation Syndrome

MCAS develops in approximately 25% of ME/CFS patients over the disease course @Wirth2023, but prevalence in general allergy practice populations remains understudied. The condition is likely underdiagnosed due to:
    - Non-specific symptoms overlapping with common allergic conditions
    - Lack of widely available, validated diagnostic criteria
    - Episodic nature making timing of testing challenging
Simple therapeutic trials with H1/H2 antihistamine combinations (e.g., loratadine + famotidine) show 72% response rates in Long COVID/ME/CFS populations, suggesting empiric trials may be both diagnostic and therapeutic for patients with treatment-resistant “allergic” symptoms.

